MODIFICATIONS BY THE DRIFT PROJECT

This is a vendored copy of librqbit 8.1.1 (from crates.io) with local
modifications, included in Drift under the terms of the Apache License 2.0
(Section 4, which permits modified distribution provided modified files carry
prominent notices stating that they were changed).

Changed files and the nature of the change:

- src/storage/filesystem/fs.rs
- src/storage/filesystem/opened_file.rs
    The default FilesystemStorage was modified so it no longer holds a
    persistent read+write file handle for the lifetime of a torrent. It now
    keeps a read-only handle for reads (used while seeding) and opens a
    short-lived read+write handle only while writing. On Windows this lets
    completed files be opened/executed by other applications while the torrent
    continues seeding (a persistent write handle otherwise blocks execution).
    A Windows-only regression test was added to fs.rs documenting the behavior.

No other files were functionally modified. The crate's webui/, examples/, and
generated lockfile were removed from this vendored copy as they are unused by
Drift (Drift builds librqbit with default features only).

The unmodified upstream project is available at the repository URL above.
